lyrics:
(Verse 1)
Gay horror, a tale untold,
Where shadows dance and fears unfold.
In moonlit nights, secrets roam free,
In the heart of darkness, we find our glee.

(Chorus)
Gay horror, a twisted delight,
Where love and fear intertwine at night.
Through the darkness, we'll brave the fright,
In this world where queer souls ignite.

(Verse 2)
In haunted halls, we find our place,
Embracing the thrill, our hearts race.
With every creak and every groan,
We stand together, not alone.
